        <headline>Severe Thunderstorm Warning issued June 6 at 4:36PM MDT until June 6 at 5:15PM MDT by NWS Goodland KS</headline>
        <description>At 436 PM MDT, a severe thunderstorm was located 8 miles southwest of
Flagler, moving east at 20 mph.

HAZARD...Ping pong ball size hail and 60 mph wind gusts.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...People and animals outdoors will be injured. Expect hail
damage to roofs, siding, windows, and vehicles. Expect wind
damage to roofs, siding, and trees.

This severe thunderstorm will remain over mainly rural areas of
southwestern Kit Carson County.

This includes Interstate 70 in Colorado between mile markers 391 and
396.
</description>
        <instruction>A Tornado Watch remains in effect until 900 PM MDT for east central
Colorado.

A tornado watch remains in effect for the warned area. Tornadoes can
develop quickly from severe thunderstorms. Although a tornado is not
immediately likely, if one is spotted act quickly and move to a place
of safety inside a sturdy structure, such as a basement or small
interior room.

For your protection move to an interior room on the lowest floor of a
building.</instruction>
